# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## [Unreleased]

### Changed
- Migrated Visualizer from JavaScript to TypeScript with strict mode (zero type errors).
- Removed legacy JS/JSX files (heartbeat.js, ChartControls.jsx, Footer.js, HeartbeatChart.jsx, checkDates.js, App.test.js).
- Converted index.js, reportWebVitals.js, setupTests.js, getClusterName.js to TypeScript.
- Centralized all configuration constants into `config.ts` (Visualizer) and environment variables (Go server).
- Separated data fetching from presentation via custom hooks and data service module.
- Structured all Go server error responses as JSON with proper HTTP status codes (400, 405, 500, 503).

### Added
- WebSocket real-time streaming (`/ws/heartbeats`) with heartbeat and alert broadcast.
- Exponential backoff reconnection in the Visualizer WebSocket hook (1s initial, 30s cap).
- Connection status indicator ("Disconnected" / "Connecting...") in the Visualizer.
- Pluggable storage interface with in-memory (default) and Redis implementations.
- Store connectivity check on server startup.
- Anomaly detection with configurable warning/critical gap thresholds.
- Alert dispatcher with webhook delivery and WebSocket broadcast.
- Toast notifications for alerts in the Visualizer (auto-dismiss after 10s).
- Zoom via click-and-drag brush selection on the chart X axis.
- Pan via Shift+drag interaction on the chart.
- "Reset Zoom" button to restore full time range.
- Multi-cluster support via ClusterSelector tabs with independent data fetching.
- Responsive chart width (280px–1920px) via ResizeObserver.
- Multiple visualization views: heatmap, timeline, histogram, node table.
- Anomaly badge component with zoom-to-anomaly support.
- Live activity panel showing real-time heartbeat and alert events.
- Semantic HTML (header, main, footer) with ARIA labels and keyboard navigation.
- Visible focus indicators (`:focus-visible`) for all interactive elements.
- Logging middleware capturing method, path, status code, and duration.
- Go server unit tests for POST/GET heartbeat handlers.
- Go server property tests (config round-trip, error responses, anomaly detection, WebSocket broadcast, POST-then-GET round-trip).
- Kubernetes client unit tests (CorrelateEBPFEvent, GenerateMockNodes, GenerateMockEBPFEvents).
- Visualizer unit tests for chartUtils (hasWarning, hasDeath) and component rendering (HeartbeatChart, ChartControls, App, Footer).
- Visualizer property tests (gap classification, anomaly detection, segment color mapping).
- Lease parser unit tests (valid parsing, malformed YAML, missing fields, round-trip).
- WebSocket E2E test for Visualizer rendering data from mocked WS stream.
- eBPF agent with cgroup resolver, probe manager, and event codec.
- eBPF programs for process monitoring, syscall tracing, and network probes.
- Simulation engine for generating realistic heartbeat data.
- Causal chain analysis and predictive alerting in the Go server.
- Helm chart and Docker deployment configs.

